## The risk-set table

Under every non-parametric estimate is one tabulation: at each distinct event time, how many
subjects are still at risk, how many have the event, and how many are censored. This risk-set
table is what Kaplan-Meier, the log-rank test, and Cox all build on, and you can compute it
directly with `event_table()`. It matches R's `survfit` tabulation.

::: {#9aa23078 .cell execution_count=16}
``` {.python .cell-code}
# Load data and build the response
lung = gw.load_dataset("lung", backend="polars")
y = gw.Surv.right(lung["time"], event=(lung["status"] == 2))

# Tabulate events and censorings at each distinct event time
gw.event_table(y).to_frame(format="polars")
```

