## Next steps

You now know how to represent survival data and how to avoid the most common coding mistake.
From here you can bring in your own data or start estimating.

- [Data sources and formats](data-sources.qmd) shows how to load data from pandas, Polars,
and other backends, how to compute durations from timestamps and encode event indicators
from compound status columns, and lists the datasets bundled with the package.
- [Estimating survival with Kaplan-Meier](kaplan-meier.qmd) shows how to estimate and
summarize the survival curve.
- [Comparing groups](comparing-groups.qmd) covers the log-rank family of tests.
- The [Quick start](quick-start.qmd) is a fast tour of everything if you prefer to skim
first.
